<p>and do all they can for the Australians many of whom, I am ashamed to say do very little to return their kindness and rather take advantage of the donors in every way possible. However the least said of that sort the better.</p>
<p>Well by 1.30 am we had just arrived in camp, the ground <strike>of</strike> everywhere covered very thickly with a hard white frost.</p>
<p>Tuesday 28th.<br/>This morning it is very cold and I can hear somebody banging at the taps to try and smash the ice in the pipe to let the water run, but the whole thing had frozen.</p>
